The paper discusses a new algorithm for improving the storage and retrieval capabilities of associative memories, which are commonly used in neural networks and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also deals with binary-weighted associative memories, which are a type of machine learning algorithm, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The proposed algorithm also involves lowering the error rate, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the advantages of the proposed algorithm for hardware implementations, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
